Description:
Ballistics of the M309 (T38) HE round fired from the US 75x408mm M20 (T21) recoilless rifle, produced in the PRC as the WB015P fired from the Type 56 recoilless rifle, respectively. Projectile is rotationally stabiilized. Loads 0.65 kg of explosives.

Projectile weighs 6.1 kg, loads 1.45 kg of 9/14 high-nitrogen, potassium propellant. Develops 310 m/s from a peak breech pressure of 510 kgf/cm^2. Chamber volume is 3.647 L and measures 3.12 dm long, 2.14 dm^2 at the rear. Nozzle throat measures 0.2748 dm^2. Projectile travels 16.54 dm in bore at a cross section of 0.4532 dm^2. Projectile drag coefficient in relation to 1943 drag curve i_43 = 1.05. One-piece cartridge weighs 8.806 kg, welded cartridge weighs 9.17 kg.

Pressure is interpreted as copper crusher gauge values.
